item.title: The Pitt season 2 episode 7 sets up the cliffhanger we all knew was coming — and it's ruined the show's most vulnerable moment to date
item.description: Since episode 2, we knew that tech was going to be a huge problem in the ER. But stupidly, The Pitt season 2 episode 7 has wiped out its most delicate moment in the process.

item.title: A $10K Bounty Awaits Anyone Who Can Hack Ring Cameras to Stop Sharing Data With Amazon
item.description: The Fulu Foundation, a nonprofit that pays out bounties for removing user-hostile features, is hunting for a way to keep Ring cameras from sending data to Amazon—without breaking the hardware.

item.title: New Research Shows AI Agents Are Running Wild Online, With Few Guardrails in Place
item.description: And this research was conducted before OpenClaw unleashed a monster.

item.title: Tesla hails the arrival of its first Cybercab – meanwhile, its Robotaxis are crashing four times more than human drivers
item.description: Would you trust Tesla's Cybercab when its Robotaxi business is posting crash data like this?

item.title: ‘I do not believe AI should do therapy’ – I asked a psychologist what worries the people trying to make AI safer
item.description: A psychologist and AI risk advisor explains the real-world risks developers and users aren’t fully seeing.

item.title: 'Toys are for play, but tech is for everything': Woody in Toy Story 5 trailer shares the awful truth
item.description: Disney and Pixar just dropped a new Toy Story 5 trailer, and now it's clear that tech truly is the villain.

item.title: Google’s new Gemini Pro model has record benchmark scores — again
item.description: Gemini 3.1 Pro promises a Google LLM capable of handling more complex forms of work.
